</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6B645C6E60FB0EAC1B405474A59244B1" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="552D0FF0935E9362A80043E8CFEAF6E6" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">
<taxonomicName id="F0C092D2576E2918AA9E8CC36905F068" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Metallophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metallophilus</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1838: 9. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="2CF03658FA16D873185160165FB3754A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">
<emphasis id="A4F1E3A0DAE895A8A347C8A1E1EE8259" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Feronia interrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828 by original designation. Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis id="07F4E43040DCFB9F7B0F2D5276CC42D4" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">metallon</emphasis>
(mine) and 
<emphasis id="6613976D8D2983A1A96811A424694308" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">philos</emphasis>
(beloved) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9998AFA13A66DB701498B4B5A34977AF" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">
<taxonomicName id="082A59D46B94CCF28D94D7AE0BFF2481" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lyperopherus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lyperopherus</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1844: 156. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="F5C07DA87DB67002AC7ACE7B5757A51E" authorityName="Gebler" authorityYear="1823" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Poecilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis id="D386FF644021AE9377F601BB0AC950EF" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Poecilus rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gebler, 1823 designated by Lindroth (1966: 525). Synonymy established by Bousquet (1999: 144). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="59320F9A7F801984A45DD2660524D111" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">lyperos</emphasis>
(painful, by extension sad) and 
<emphasis id="8893F21809B7A2739F3CDC413549D250" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">phero</emphasis>
(to bear, carry) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EFE79285F65C3CBD5532560A2CE5F967" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">
<taxonomicName id="4B3986CF8E86547F6F55AB0E55798615" authorityName="O. Berlov" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tundraphilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tundraphilus</taxonomicName>
O. Berlov, 1996: 12. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="B4D4511A9A7FEE4FF3AA1D950CFFA797" authorityName="J. Sahlberg" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublaevis">
<emphasis id="CC50A52FC9A18C1770E3E40C36EB0E0E" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Feronia sublaevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sahlberg, 1880 by original designation. Synonymy established by Bousquet (1999: 144). Etymology. From the English name tundra (treeless ecosystem of the arctic regions) and the Greek 
<emphasis id="9E907A45E824696A1A83180E3470FE74" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">philos</emphasis>
(beloved) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6FC8D9B4CEA9673AE4EEE3FE4E0A0EDD" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="05D4B0244A9AFF969F279896A06E3F77" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F46DA8597FA9D3C7023E159DF352F891" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Eight species in North America (one Holarctic species) and Palaearctic Asia (eight species, one extending to European Russia).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="546A871C61B41ACEB8090D23D96FA412" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="80CD01F7A54CC78DDF05F4AB207936DD" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD646CE68361FB42DA6E08B9E8BD01A2" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">
According to Bousquet (1999: 145), this group is closely related and possibly paraphyletic in regard to 
<taxonomicName id="C4B6924F68305F1C8E50EDDFB7F8ACBE" authorityName="Megerle &amp; Steven" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Myosodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B664EEA709B627E0332840E3B8538C54" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Myosodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fischer von Waldheim, a subgenus of 22 species centered in the Caucasus Mountains. Brinev and Shilenkov (2001) retained 
<taxonomicName id="4ADD801509DA40CA04CF1117160E1BA0" authorityName="O. Berlov" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tundraphilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66E4DC4EE93E4C5CC671BE232A06DDF6" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Tundraphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid subgenus, listing 
<taxonomicName id="4D08DFFB73EA06A467639EBD2C973B2A" baseAuthorityName="Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublaevis">
<emphasis id="58FC72F573E58A38503ED3F316192945" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Pterostichus sublaevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sahlberg, 
<taxonomicName id="52C5EF0E579220E498CE096A469A4376" baseAuthorityName="Chaudoir" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orion">
<emphasis id="0E216FD6E1738778E4776B098C666B72" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Pterostichus orion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="0605704DD1C78173D9A066F202ED329E" originalValue="Tschitschérine">Tschitscherine</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName id="42344E1E739C52EC60DF05C209AE18FD" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pfitzenmayeri">
<emphasis id="D2639C1A093CF2E9C6C76DC0E3E4E696" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Pterostichus pfitzenmayeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poppius, and 
<taxonomicName id="D3BB2573218524EA3BE758B182858758" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1860" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamtschaticus">
<emphasis id="9F3C3454AE837DF7BD18907E6D677208" italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">Pterostichus kamtschaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky in it.
</paragraph>
